Mt Vernon is not in what today can be considered "northern" Baltimore.  300 years ago that would've been the case!  It is geographically below the center of the city boundaries - and would therefore be "southern" Baltimore - or really mid-Baltimore.  Baltimore street was originally the north-south dividing line for Baltimore and Mt Vernon is literally 2 blocks north of that street.  No one thinks of that area as "northern" Baltimore because it simply is not.

I removed part of the first sentence which described Tiffany Trump as a 'socialite'. Correct me if I'm being unreasonable! I understand if some people disagree with this edit, but I think it would be more appropriate not to describe her as a socialite in the first sentence.
